They have world tour dates in France, Spain, Italy, Switzerland, Austria, the Czech Republic and Japan through July 27th. The band then returns stateside for North American dates beginning July 31st in Louisville, Kentucky. If you're noticing the theme here is a bunch of firsts, rest assured that the band's latest project was not its first to experience success. It was the band's second studio album, 2001's "Three," that reached the top 30 in the Australian album charts and achieved platinum sales, charting a course of success over the next decade. Their subsequent albums, "Sunrise Over Sea," "Grand National," and "April Uprising" all debuted at number one on the Australian album charts, and their first-ever live album also reached the Top Ten.
